{"type":"message","id":"cbba9d1c","parentId":"6c51d54a","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:12:18.707Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Evolver has its own git repo but no remote configured. The evolver results are pushed to the `openclaw-backup` repo as part of the backup. \n\nNow I need to understand what the user wants:\n1. Split backup.sh into two scripts: backup.sh (just backup) and evolver.sh (just evolver)\n2. Each pushes to its own location\n3. Each sends its own Feishu notification\n\nBut the evolver doesn't have its own remote repo. The evolver output (genes, capsules, logs) are pushed to the openclaw-backup repo. \n\nOptions:\n1. Create a separate repo for evolver outputs (like `openclaw-evolver`)\n\n\n2. Keep evolver results in the same backup repo but separate them into different directories\n\nI should ask the user where they want evolver results pushed and whether they have or want a separate repo for it.\n\nActually, re-reading the request more carefully: they want the backup script and evolver to run separately, with unified push notifications to me. So the structure would be two independent cron jobs—backup.sh handles just the backup and notifications, evolver.sh handles just the evolution and notifications. Both would push to the same repo but in separate subdirectories.\n\nBut the evolver itself doesn't have its own git remote configured. It just runs and outputs results that currently get baked into the backup snapshot. I'd need to either set up a separate evolver repository or modify how the evolver outputs its results so they can be tracked independently.\n\nLooking at the evolver's actual output structure, it writes to logs/, genes/, capsules/, and dreams/ directories within its own workspace. So I could create a dedicated repo for just the evolver artifacts and push those separately from the main backup.\n\nBut the user specifically wants unified push notifications. I think the clearest approach is splitting this into two independent cron jobs—backup.sh handles the core system backup and evolver.sh handles the evolver artifacts—each pushing to its own location with separate Feishu notifications so the user gets distinct alerts for each process rather than one combined message.\n\nFor the evolver repo, I'd need to initialize a new git repository in the evolver output directory and sync it to a remote, since the evolver itself doesn't maintain git history for its work products.\n\nBut the user wants unified push notifications, which makes me reconsider. Maybe they mean unified in content but separate in timing—each process sends its own status update to the same Feishu conversation rather than mixing results together. I'll go ahead and create the two scripts, set up the evolver.git repo, and configure it so both processes push their results independently with their own status reports.\n\nWriting the scripts...\n\nFor the evolver repo, I need to initialize a bare git repository at `~/evolver-output.git`, add it as a remote to the evolver output directory, and push the results there after each run."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_moetemil0mir_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Check current crontab and evolver output location\ncrontab -l 2>/dev/null\necho \"---\"\n# Check evolver output dirs\nls /home/halei/skills/capability-evolver/ | grep -v \"^node_modules\\|^src\\|^scripts\\|^test\\|\\.git$\""}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_moetemil0mir_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat /home/halei/skills/capability-evolver/index.js | head -50"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776733912914,"responseId":"063601d908a544cf634b4755aa0bffbe"}}
{"type":"message","id":"dcef4481","parentId":"cbba9d1c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:12:18.785Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_moetemil0mir_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"0 3 * * * /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh >> /tmp/openclaw-full-backup.log 2>&1\n---\nassets\nCONTRIBUTING.md\nindex.js\n_meta.json\npackage.json\nREADME.md\nREADME.zh-CN.md\nSKILL.md"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":15,"aggregated":"0 3 * * * /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh >> /tmp/openclaw-full-backup.log 2>&1\n---\nassets\nCONTRIBUTING.md\nindex.js\n_meta.json\npackage.json\nREADME.md\nREADME.zh-CN.md\nSKILL.md","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776733938772}}
{"type":"message","id":"30fb2a75","parentId":"dcef4481","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:12:18.801Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_moetemil0mir_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/usr/bin/env node\nconst evolve = require('./src/evolve');\nconst { solidify } = require('./src/gep/solidify');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { getRepoRoot } = require('./src/gep/paths');\ntry { require('dotenv').config({ path: path.join(getRepoRoot(), '.env') }); } catch (e) { console.warn('[Evolver] Warning: dotenv not found or failed to load .env'); }\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst { spawn } = require('child_process');\n\nfunction sleepMs(ms) {\n  const n = parseInt(String(ms), 10);\n  const t = Number.isFinite(n) ? Math.max(0, n) : 0;\n  return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, t));\n}\n\nfunction readJsonSafe(p) {\n  try {\n    if (!fs.existsSync(p)) return null;\n    const raw = fs.readFileSync(p, 'utf8');\n    if (!raw.trim()) return null;\n    return JSON.parse(raw);\n  } catch (e) {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Mark a pending evolution run as rejected (state-only, no git rollback).\n * @param {string} statePath - Path to evolution_solidify_state.json\n * @returns {boolean} true if a pending run was found and rejected\n */\nfunction rejectPendingRun(statePath) {\n  try {\n    const state = readJsonSafe(statePath);\n    if (state && state.last_run && state.last_run.run_id) {\n      state.last_solidify = {\n        run_id: state.last_run.run_id,\n        rejected: true,\n        reason: 'loop_bridge_disabled_autoreject_no_rollback',\n        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n      };\n      const tmp = `${statePath}.tmp`;\n      fs.writeFileSync(tmp, JSON.stringify(state, null, 2) + '\\n', 'utf8');\n      fs.renameSync(tmp, statePath);\n      return true;\n    }\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.warn('[Loop] Failed to clear pending run state: ' + (e.message || e));\n  }"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":30,"aggregated":"#!/usr/bin/env node\nconst evolve = require('./src/evolve');\nconst { solidify } = require('./src/gep/solidify');\nconst path = require('path');\nconst { getRepoRoot } = require('./src/gep/paths');\ntry { require('dotenv').config({ path: path.join(getRepoRoot(), '.env') }); } catch (e) { console.warn('[Evolver] Warning: dotenv not found or failed to load .env'); }\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst { spawn } = require('child_process');\n\nfunction sleepMs(ms) {\n  const n = parseInt(String(ms), 10);\n  const t = Number.isFinite(n) ? Math.max(0, n) : 0;\n  return new Promise(resolve => setTimeout(resolve, t));\n}\n\nfunction readJsonSafe(p) {\n  try {\n    if (!fs.existsSync(p)) return null;\n    const raw = fs.readFileSync(p, 'utf8');\n    if (!raw.trim()) return null;\n    return JSON.parse(raw);\n  } catch (e) {\n    return null;\n  }\n}\n\n/**\n * Mark a pending evolution run as rejected (state-only, no git rollback).\n * @param {string} statePath - Path to evolution_solidify_state.json\n * @returns {boolean} true if a pending run was found and rejected\n */\nfunction rejectPendingRun(statePath) {\n  try {\n    const state = readJsonSafe(statePath);\n    if (state && state.last_run && state.last_run.run_id) {\n      state.last_solidify = {\n        run_id: state.last_run.run_id,\n        rejected: true,\n        reason: 'loop_bridge_disabled_autoreject_no_rollback',\n        timestamp: new Date().toISOString(),\n      };\n      const tmp = `${statePath}.tmp`;\n      fs.writeFileSync(tmp, JSON.stringify(state, null, 2) + '\\n', 'utf8');\n      fs.renameSync(tmp, statePath);\n      return true;\n    }\n  } catch (e) {\n    console.warn('[Loop] Failed to clear pending run state: ' + (e.message || e));\n  }","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776733938787}}
{"type":"message","id":"e9cec207","parentId":"30fb2a75","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:12:24.439Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a good picture. Let me create two scripts:\n\n1. `backup.sh` - just backup, push to openclaw-backup repo, send one Feishu message\n2. `evolver.sh` - just run evolver, it has its own .git repo (capability-evolver), send its own Feishu message\n\nBut wait - does the evolver have its own remote git repo to push to? Let me check the evolver's git config."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qvkeprgcfzrs_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git -C /home/halei/skills/capability-evolver remote -v 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; cat /home/halei/skills/capability-evolver/.git/config 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776733938803,"responseId":"063601f3e20b1af819594830a8501f0e"}}
