{"type":"message","id":"92474df9","parentId":"3d148c11","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:13:16.864Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Evolver has no remote - it's a local git repo without a remote. So the evolver results are NOT being pushed anywhere currently. They go into logs/ directory within the evolver directory.\n\nNow let me understand what HALEI wants:\n\n1. Split backup.sh and evolver into two separate scripts\n2. Backup script → pushes to openclaw-backup repo, sends its own Feishu message\n3. Evolver script → runs evolver, sends its own Feishu message (but where does it push? It has no remote)\n\nWait, actually reading the log more carefully:\n\n\nThe evolver ran and produced output to logs/status_undefined.json and logs/gep_events/, but since there's no remote configured, nothing actually gets pushed anywhere. The evolver changes live in the evolver directory itself. So what HALEI probably wants is to have the backup script focus only on backup tasks and send a message when that's done, then have a separate evolver script that runs the evolver and sends its own notification about what changed.\n\nFor the evolver piece, I need to figure out where those changes should live. The evolver directory is at `/home/halei/skills/capability-evolver/`, but I'm not sure if that's the right place for evolved assets to accumulate, or if there's a separate memory/evolution directory that should be getting the output instead.\n\nLooking at the file paths referenced in the logs, the gep_prompt files and status_undefined.json are being written to `/home/halei/memory/evolution/`, so that's likely where evolved genes and capsules are being stored. The evolver itself is cloning/pulling from GitHub for the backup repo, but the actual evolution artifacts aren't being pushed anywhere - they're just accumulating locally. The evolver is a sub-module within the openclaw-backup repo structure, so when the main repo pushes, the evolver changes get included in that snapshot. But HALEI wants to separate them. I need to split this into two distinct scripts: one for backup that sends its own Feishu notification, and another for evolver that handles its own separate push and notification. The evolver will need its own repository to push to, which I don't have set up yet. Let me first split the scripts as requested, then figure out the evolver's separate remote repository. the evolver output somewhere meaningful\n3. Send a unified Feishu notification for each\n\nActually, re-reading the request: \"统一推送给我\" - they want unified notifications. So maybe they want:\n- Backup done → message: \"备份完成\"\n- Evolver done → message: \"EVO完成\" \n\nOr maybe they want to see both results in one message.\n\nActually I think \"统一推送给我\" means \"push to me uniformly\" in the sense of \"send me updates in a consistent way\" - i.e., both should send Feishu messages. Not necessarily combined into one.\n\nLet me proceed with splitting them and giving each its own Feishu notification.\n\nFor the evolver, I need to figure out where to push. Since it has no remote, maybe I should use the openclaw-backup repo but with a different branch or subfolder? But that would couple them again.\n\nOr maybe the evolver doesn't need to push anywhere - the evolver's work is ephemeral (it analyzes sessions and generates genes/capsules in memory). It doesn't need to persist to a remote because the evolver directory itself is already backed up by the backup script.\n\nThe evolver creates genes/capsules and logs. The genes get stored in memory/evolution/ which is already part of the backup. So maybe the split is simply:\n- backup.sh: just backup (already includes the evolver dir in the rsync)\n- evolver.sh: just run evolver and send notification\n\nThis way evolver results are captured in the daily backup snapshot.\n\nLet me create evolver.sh now."},{"type":"text","text":"明白了。Evolver 没有自己的 remote，它的结果其实是跟着 backup 快照一起 push 的。拆分策略：\n\n- **backup.sh** — 只做备份，发一条消息\n- **evolver.sh** — 独立跑 evolver，发另一条消息（结果下次 backup 快照会包进去）\n\n两个脚本还是写到一起，只需要改 backup.sh，把 evolver 那段拆出去单独调度：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jb89niacljig_1","name":"write","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh","content":"#!/bin/bash\n# OpenClaw Daily Backup Script (v3.1 — 2026-04-21)\n# 只做备份，不跑 evolver\n\nBACKUP_REPO=\"/tmp/openclaw-backup-clone\"\nOPENCLAW_DIR=\"$HOME/.openclaw\"\nGIT_REF=\"main\"\nDATE_DIR=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\n\nGH_TOKEN=$(grep \"oauth_token:\" ~/.config/gh/hosts.yml | awk '{print $2}')\n\necho \"[$(date)] Starting OpenClaw backup...\"\n\n# Clone or update backup repo\nif [ -d \"$BACKUP_REPO/.git\" ]; then\n  cd \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\n  git checkout \"$GIT_REF\" 2>/dev/null\n  git pull origin \"$GIT_REF\" --quiet\nelse\n  rm -rf \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\n  git clone \"https://${GH_TOKEN}@github.com/59330857/openclaw-backup.git\" \"$BACKUP_REPO\" --quiet\nfi\n\n# Fresh date dir (replace old snapshot entirely)\nrm -rf \"$BACKUP_REPO/$DATE_DIR\"\nmkdir -p \"$BACKUP_REPO/$DATE_DIR\"\n\n# rsync helper: dest always inside $DATE_DIR/\ndo_rsync() {\n  local src=\"$1\"\n  local dst=\"$2\"   # relative to $DATE_DIR/\n  if [ -e \"$src\" ]; then\n    rsync -a --exclude='.git' \"$src\" \"$BACKUP_REPO/$DATE_DIR/$dst\"\n  fi\n}\n\n# 1. Core config files (no trailing slash = copy as file)\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openclaw.json\" \"\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openclaw.json.bak\" \"\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openclaw.json.bak.1\" \"\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openviking.env\" \"\"\n\n# 2. Directories (trailing slash = copy contents)\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/agents/\" \"agents/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/credentials/\" \"credentials/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/cron/\" \"cron/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/devices/\" \"devices/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/flows/\" \"flows/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/identity/\" \"identity/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/feishu/\" \"feishu/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/subagents/\" \"subagents/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/extensions/\" \"extensions/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/skills/\" \"skills/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace/\" \"workspace/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-main/\" \"workspace-main/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/memory/\" \"memory/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/.evomap/\" \"evomap/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/qqbot/\" \"qqbot/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openclaw-weixin/\" \"openclaw-weixin/\"\n\n# Commit and push\ncd \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\nif [ -n \"$(git status --porcelain)\" ]; then\n  git config user.email \"backup@openclaw\"\n  git config user.name \"OpenClaw Backup\"\n  git add -A\n  git commit -m \"Full backup $DATE_DIR $(date '+%H:%M')\"\n  git push origin \"$GIT_REF\"\n  echo \"[$(date)] Backup pushed to GitHub\"\n\n  # ── Send Feishu notification ──────────────────────────────────────\n  APP_ID=\"cli_a93650c6fc785bce\"\n  APP_SECRET=\"I6PGaAjXEqMW81COlOcRzc7zpdd2qqOV\"\n  USER_OPEN_ID=\"ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb\"\n\n  TOKEN_RESP=$(curl -s -X POST \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/auth/v3/tenant_access_token/internal\" \\\n    -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n    -d \"{\\\"app_id\\\":\\\"$APP_ID\\\",\\\"app_secret\\\":\\\"$APP_SECRET\\\"}\")\n  ACCESS_TOKEN=$(echo $TOKEN_RESP | python3 -c \"import json,sys; print(json.load(sys.stdin).get('tenant_access_token',''))\")\n\n  if [ -n \"$ACCESS_TOKEN\" ]; then\n    NOTIF_MSG=\"✅ 每日备份完成\\n\\n📦 备份 → 已推送至 openclaw-backup\"\n    curl -s -X POST \"https://open.feishu.cn/open-apis/im/v1/messages?receive_id_type=open_id\" \\\n      -H \"Authorization: Bearer $ACCESS_TOKEN\" \\\n      -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n      -d \"{\n        \\\"receive_id\\\":\\\"$USER_OPEN_ID\\\",\n        \\\"msg_type\\\":\\\"text\\\",\n        \\\"content\\\":\\\"{\\\\\\\"text\\\\\\\":\\\\\\\"$NOTIF_MSG\\\\\\\"}\\\"\n      }\" > /dev/null 2>&1\n    echo \"[$(date)] Backup Feishu notification sent\"\n  else\n    echo \"[$(date)] Failed to get access token, skipping Feishu notification\"\n  fi\n  # ── End Feishu notification ────────────────────────────────────────\nelse\n  echo \"[$(date)] No changes, skipping commit\"\nfi\n"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776733944485,"responseId":"063601f8561606b3123fdd363355099c"}}
