{"type":"message","id":"a45dcffd","parentId":"55f8fe73","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:23:40.823Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_mcb2f735d376_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-lark\",\n  \"channels\": [\"feishu\"],\n  \"skills\": [\"./skills\"],\n  \"configSchema\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"additionalProperties\": false,\n    \"properties\": {}\n  },\n  \"channelConfigs\": {\n    \"feishu\": {\n      \"schema\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}---\n/home/halei/.openclaw/openviking.env\n/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/.agents/skills/1688-product-search/.env\n/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/.agents/skills/1688-ranking/.env"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":57,"aggregated":"{\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-lark\",\n  \"channels\": [\"feishu\"],\n  \"skills\": [\"./skills\"],\n  \"configSchema\": {\n    \"type\": \"object\",\n    \"additionalProperties\": false,\n    \"properties\": {}\n  },\n  \"channelConfigs\": {\n    \"feishu\": {\n      \"schema\": {\n        \"type\": \"object\"\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}---\n/home/halei/.openclaw/openviking.env\n/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/.agents/skills/1688-product-search/.env\n/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/.agents/skills/1688-ranking/.env","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776734620808}}
{"type":"message","id":"f447083b","parentId":"a45dcffd","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:23:56.815Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the feishu plugin doesn't have its own app_id/app_secret - these are managed by OpenClaw's internal configuration, which I can't access. The plugin receives messages and sends via the kiit bot.\n\nThe backup script uses a hardcoded `cli_a93650c6fc785bce` - that's the backup bot, separate from kiit.\n\nTo send messages to kiit's conversation from a script, the backup script would need to somehow use kiit's identity. But that requires either:\n1. kiit's app credentials (which I can't see due to security restrictions)\n2. Some internal OpenClaw API for sending messages as the kiit agent\n\n\n3. The OpenClaw framework likely has a built-in messaging API that the feishu plugin uses internally, which would be the proper way to send messages to kiit's conversation rather than trying to access credentials directly. I should look for documentation on how to use this internal API.\n\nThe cleanest approach would probably be to create a dedicated notification agent that the cron jobs can invoke, which would then handle sending the message through the feishu plugin's internal API rather than making external API calls.\n\nLooking at the feishu skills available, I could leverage feishu-im-read to find the conversation ID and feishu-message to send the notification, which would route through the kiit bot instead of needing separate credentials."},{"type":"text","text":"feishu 插件用的是 kiit 的身份（`openclaw-lark`），我没权限看到它的 credentials。备份脚本里的 `cli_a93650c6fc785bce` 是另一个 app，所以发到另一个对话。\n\n有两个方案：\n\n**方案 A（推荐）：用 OpenClaw 官方 feishu 发消息接口**\n备份脚本改成调用 OpenClaw 的内部 API，让 kiit 来发这条消息。这样你在 kiit 窗口能直接看到。\n\n**方案 B：继续用备份 bot 发，但引导你找到那个对话**\n备份 bot 发的消息在另一个单独对话里，不是 kiit 这个窗口。\n\n我先试方案 A，看 feishu 插件有没有暴露发送接口：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_znadektmbbuv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -r \"sendMessage\\|postMe