{"type":"message","id":"e90c4f79","parentId":"5b3302b5","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:24:56.856Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_zt7le332ye8s_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"/**\n * Copyright (c) 2026 ByteDance Ltd. and/or its affiliates\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\n *\n * Feishu / Lark SDK client management.\n *\n * Provides `LarkClient` — a unified manager for Lark SDK client instances,\n * WebSocket connections, EventDispatcher lifecycle, and bot identity.\n *\n * Consumers obtain instances via factory methods:\n *   - `LarkClient.fromCfg(cfg, accountId)` — resolve account from config\n *   - `LarkClient.fromAccount(account)` — from a pre-resolved account\n *   - `LarkClient.fromCredentials(credentials)` — ephemeral instance (not cached)\n */\nimport * as Lark from '@larksuiteoapi/node-sdk';\nimport type { ClawdbotConfig, PluginRuntime } from 'openclaw/plugin-sdk';\nimport type { MessageDedup } from '../messaging/inbound/dedup';\nimport type { FeishuProbeResult, LarkAccount, LarkBrand } from './types';\n/** Credential set accepted by the ephemeral `fromCredentials` factory. */\nexport interface LarkClientCredentials {\n    accountId?: string;\n    appId?: string;\n    appSecret?: string;\n    brand?: LarkBrand;\n}\nexport declare class LarkClient {\n    readonly account: LarkAccount;\n    private _sdk;\n    private _wsClient;\n    private _botOpenId;\n    private _botName;\n    private _lastProbeResult;\n    private _lastProbeAt;\n    /** Attached message deduplicator — disposed together with the client. */\n    messageDedup: MessageDedup | null;\n    /** Persist the runtime instance for later retrieval (activate 阶段调用一次). */\n    static setRuntime(runtime: PluginRuntime): void;\n    /** Retrieve the stored runtime instance. Throws if not yet initialised. */\n    static get runtime(): PluginRuntime;\n    private static _globalConfig;\n    /** Store the original global config (called during monitor startup). */\n    static setGlobalConfig(cfg: ClawdbotConfig): void;\n    /** Retrieve the stored global config, or `null` if not yet set. */\n    static get globalConfig(): ClawdbotConfig | null;\n    private constructor();\n    /** Shorthand for `this.account.accountId`. */\n    get accountId(): string;\n    /** Resolve account from config and return a cached `LarkClient`. */\n    static fromCfg(cfg: ClawdbotConfig, accountId?: string): LarkClient;\n    /**\n     * Get (or create) a cached `LarkClient` for the given account.\n     * If the cached instance has stale credentials it is replaced.\n     */\n    static fromAccount(account: LarkAccount): LarkClient;\n    /**\n     * Create an ephemeral `LarkClient` from bare credentials.\n     * The instance is **not** added to the global cache — suitable for\n     * one-off probe / diagnose calls that should not pollute account state.\n     */\n    static fromCredentials(credentials: LarkClientCredentials): LarkClient;"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":11,"aggregated":"/**\n * Copyright (c) 2026 ByteDance Ltd. and/or its affiliates\n * SPDX-License-Identifier: MIT\n *\n * Feishu / Lark SDK client management.\n *\n * Provides `LarkClient` — a unified manager for Lark SDK client instances,\n * WebSocket connections, EventDispatcher lifecycle, and bot identity.\n *\n * Consumers obtain instances via factory methods:\n *   - `LarkClient.fromCfg(cfg, accountId)` — resolve account from config\n *   - `LarkClient.fromAccount(account)` — from a pre-resolved account\n *   - `LarkClient.fromCredentials(credentials)` — ephemeral instance (not cached)\n */\nimport * as Lark from '@larksuiteoapi/node-sdk';\nimport type { ClawdbotConfig, PluginRuntime } from 'openclaw/plugin-sdk';\nimport type { MessageDedup } from '../messaging/inbound/dedup';\nimport type { FeishuProbeResult, LarkAccount, LarkBrand } from './types';\n/** Credential set accepted by the ephemeral `fromCredentials` factory. */\nexport interface LarkClientCredentials {\n    accountId?: string;\n    appId?: string;\n    appSecret?: string;\n    brand?: LarkBrand;\n}\nexport declare class LarkClient {\n    readonly account: LarkAccount;\n    private _sdk;\n    private _wsClient;\n    private _botOpenId;\n    private _botName;\n    private _lastProbeResult;\n    private _lastProbeAt;\n    /** Attached message deduplicator — disposed together with the client. */\n    messageDedup: MessageDedup | null;\n    /** Persist the runtime instance for later retrieval (activate 阶段调用一次). */\n    static setRuntime(runtime: PluginRuntime): void;\n    /** Retrieve the stored runtime instance. Throws if not yet initialised. */\n    static get runtime(): PluginRuntime;\n    private static _globalConfig;\n    /** Store the original global config (called during monitor startup). */\n    static setGlobalConfig(cfg: ClawdbotConfig): void;\n    /** Retrieve the stored global config, or `null` if not yet set. */\n    static get globalConfig(): ClawdbotConfig | null;\n    private constructor();\n    /** Shorthand for `this.account.accountId`. */\n    get accountId(): string;\n    /** Resolve account from config and return a cached `LarkClient`. */\n    static fromCfg(cfg: ClawdbotConfig, accountId?: string): LarkClient;\n    /**\n     * Get (or create) a cached `LarkClient` for the given account.\n     * If the cached instance has stale credentials it is replaced.\n     */\n    static fromAccount(account: LarkAccount): LarkClient;\n    /**\n     * Create an ephemeral `LarkClient` from bare credentials.\n     * The instance is **not** added to the global cache — suitable for\n     * one-off probe / diagnose calls that should not pollute account state.\n     */\n    static fromCredentials(credentials: LarkClientCredentials): LarkClient;","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776734696843}}
{"type":"message","id":"794b1183","parentId":"e90c4f79","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:25:08.186Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see there's a `LarkClient.fromCredentials` that takes `appId` and `appSecret`. The kiit feishu credentials must be stored somewhere in a config file. Let me look for how the feishu plugin is actually configured with credentials - they must be in the plugin's own config files. Let me check if there's a `feishu-kiit` credential file or something similar.\n\nActually wait - let me look at what files are in the `credentials` directory more carefully and see if there's a way to get the kiit app credentials.\n\nActually, I think the approach here should be simpler. Since kiit is running as the main session and has access to the feishu plugin, I could potentially look at how feishu-post or feishu-card works in the evolver wrapper to understand how messages get sent via the kiit identity. Let me check the evolver's report.js.\n\n\nBut I don't have access to that wrapper code either. Let me step back and think about this differently. Rather than trying to access the kiit app credentials directly, maybe the backup script should just send notifications to the user in a more straightforward way. Looking at what the user actually said - they're not getting the messages in the kiit conversation, which means the backup script is likely using the wrong bot identity to send them. The simplest approach might be to find where feishu-post or feishu-card is actually configured and use that directly."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sh7enihrtcou_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"feishu-post*\" -o -name \"feishuCard*\" -o -name \"card*\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v node_modules | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_sh7enihrtcou_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/extensions/openclaw-lark/src/"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"Mi