{"type":"message","id":"5125494a","parentId":"77d5b78e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:26:16.581Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The `openclaw acp` is a client tool, not something that lets me send messages programmatically from a shell script.\n\nLet me think about this differently. The feishu plugin has a tool called `feishu_im_user_message` that can send messages. This is one of the registered tools. But this tool is meant for ME (the AI agent) to call during conversation, not for a cron script to call.\n\nThe real issue is that the backup script needs to send a Feishu message to the user via the kiit bot. The kiit bot is the `openclaw-lark` plugin. The credentials for kiit are managed by that plugin.\n \nI could try accessing the kiit bot's credentials directly from the pairing file, but those are encrypted or contain WebSocket tokens rather than HTTP API credentials. Let me check what the feishu plugin actually stores in its credentials directory to understand what format they're in."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fx3izj5qbf21_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/.openclaw/feishu/ 2>/dev/null; find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.json\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" -not -path \"*/.git/*\" | xargs grep -l \"app_id\\|appId\\|app_secret\\|appSecret\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"package\\|\\.map\" | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776734766641,"responseId":"0636052ff41d0da2da9560c94008eed9"}}
