\\"\\uff0c\\u6240\\u4ee5\\u6211\\u6ca1\\u6709\\u6279\\u51c6\\u4efb\\u4f55\\u64cd\\u4f5c\\u3002\\n\\n\\u5f85\\u6279\\u51c6\\u7684\\u64cd\\u4f5c\\uff1a\\n1. \\u5220\\u9664 `TTS-\\u9009\\u54c1\\u4e13\\u5bb6-SOUL.md`\\n2. \\u64a4\\u9500 workspace \\u6240\\u6709\\u672a\\u63d0\\u4ea4\\u6539\\u52a8\\n3. \\u6e05\\u7a7a agents/ \\u76ee\\u5f55\\n\\n**\\u8fd9\\u4e9b\\u64cd\\u4f5c\\u76ee\\u524d\\u5168\\u90e8\\u6682\\u505c**\\uff0c\\u914d\\u7f6e\\u6587\\u4ef6\\u4fdd\\u6301\\u539f\\u6837\\u3002\\u5982\\u679c\\u4f60\\u60f3\\u7ee7\\u7eed\\u8fd9\\u4e9b\\u64cd\\u4f5c\\uff0c\\u56de\\u590d\\u6211\\u6279\\u51c6\\u5373\\u53ef \\u2705\",\n      \"mediaUrls\": []\n    }\n  ],\n  \"threadId\": null,\n  \"replyToId\": null,\n  \"bestEffort\": false,\n  \"retryCount\": 5,\n  \"lastAttemptAt\": 1775298788351,\n  \"lastError\": \"LarkClient[default]: appId and appSecret are required\"\n}","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776734780449}}
{"type":"message","id":"4ba4016f","parentId":"7805024a","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:26:47.302Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Found it! The delivery queue failed because `appId and appSecret are required` for the default account. This means there's a delivery queue system in OpenClaw that tries to send messages through the feishu plugin's LarkClient, but it can't because the default feishu app credentials aren't configured.\n\nThe interesting thing is: this failed delivery is from the \"default\" account, but kiit works. This means kiit uses a different account id. Let me look at the feishu credentials more carefully to find which account is kiit.\n\nActually, the `accountId: \"default\"` in the failed delivery suggests that messages sent through the system use the \"default\" feishu account. But kiit works because maybe kiit uses a different mechanism (the openclaw-lark plugin with its own credentials stored somewhere).\n \nWait, if `openclaw-lark` is enabled but `plugins.entries.feishu` is disabled, then kiit must be receiving messages through the openclaw-lark plugin's WebSocket connection rather than the Feishu webhook endpoint. The delivery queue's \"default\" account is separate from this, which is why it can't find the appId/appSecret it needs.\n\nBut here's the thing—the failed delivery is from back in March (with an enqueuedAt of ~1775114142755, which converts to early April), and kiit is working right now. So this failure might be stale. Let me reconsider how the backup.sh script actually sends messages: it calls the Feishu API directly using appId = cli_a93650c6fc785bce with appSecret = I6PGaAjXEqMW81COlOcRzc7zpdd2qqOV, not through OpenClaw's internal system at all. That delivery queue failure was likely just a one-time issue that doesn't affect the current operation.\n\nSo kiit is actually a separate Feishu app entirely. The backup script uses the cli_a93650c6fc785bce app, which is the \"default\" account and appears to be the one sending those queued delivery messages. Kiit uses a different app, which is why it's working independently.\n\nLooking at the credentials folder, there's a feishu-kiit-allowFrom.json file, but the failed delivery shows accountId = \"default\". This suggests the system has multiple Feishu apps configured—one for kiit and one for the backup script—and they're separate enough that HALEI might not have realized they were looking at different app contexts in the Feishu portal.\n\nRather than continuing to dig through credentials, the more practical solution is to just send a test message using the kiit credentials if they're accessible, or check the feishu credentials directory for the kiit-specific app information."},{"type":"text","text":"找到问题了。delivery queue 里有个失败消息用的是 `default` 账号（没有 appId/appSecret），但 kiit 是另一个 app。这个队列消息是很久前失败的，说明系统里有两个飞书 app：\n\n- **kiit** — 你现在聊天的这个（openclaw-lark）\n- **default** — 备份脚本在用的那个（cli_a93650c6fc785bce）\n\n我来找一下 kiit 的 app 凭证：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y6eya0zd39w7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.json\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" -not -path \"*/.git/*\" | xargs grep -l \"app_id\\|appId\\|app_id\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"package\\|\\.map\\|openclaw.json\\|delivery\" | head -10"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_y6eya0zd39w7_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"find ~/.openclaw -name \"*.json\" -not -path \"*/node_modules/*\" -not -path \"*/.git/*\" | xargs grep -l \"cli_\\|lark\\|feishu\" 2>/dev/null | grep -v \"package\\|\\.map\\|delivery\" | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776734780469,"responseId":"0636053db969fd402de7d815d1214ea2"}}
