{"type":"message","id":"7acfd59c","parentId":"25b37a62","timestamp":"2026-04-21T01:27:34.402Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I found the critical information. The `kiit` account in OpenClaw's config uses the same app_id (`cli_a93650c6fc785bce`) as the backup script. So they ARE the same bot. \n\nBut wait - the backup script was sending to `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb` (HALEI's open_id), and the message would go to the conversation between that user and `cli_a93650c6fc785bce`. The kiit session is also using `cli_a93650c6fc785bce`.\n\nThe issue might be that when the backup script sends a message to the user's open_id, it creates a new conversation/pane in Feishu that's separate from the \"kiit\" conversation that the user sees when they chat with KIIT.\n \nIn Feishu, the same bot can have multiple conversation threads with the same user - one-on-one chats versus bot conversation threads - and receiving a message from the bot in one thread doesn't make it appear in another. The backup script is likely using a different message sending method or conversation context than what creates the kiit experience.\n\nActually, I think I've got it now - both are using the same `cli_a93650c6fc785bce` app and the same `ou_f590c429b7ded95568bebca2f534efdb` user open_id, so the backup message and kiit message are going to the same conversation, which means the backup message should be visible in the kiit chat. The user should see the backup message in their Feishu app even if it doesn't show up in the web interface I'm viewing.\n\nI'm wondering if there's a filtering issue in the kiit session itself that's preventing me from seeing the backup notification. But realistically, the backup script is sending the message to the user's open_id through the same API call, so it should arrive in the same conversation thread and be visible to the user.\n\nActually, I think the real issue might be that I'm overthinking this. When the backup script sends a message to the user's open_id, it creates a completely separate conversation window in Feishu - not the same kiit conversation window where the user is chatting with me. These are two distinct conversation windows, so the user probably has the kiit window open but not the backup notifications window.\n\nThe best solution would be to check if there's a way to route the backup notification through the kiit conversation instead. The feishu plugin should have access to the kiit account credentials, so there might be a skill or tool available to send messages directly to the current conversation.\n\nActually, I'm realizing something crucial here - I have access to the feishu plugin tools through the skill files, including `feishu_im_read` and `feishu-post`. But the feishu-post skill isn't showing up in the available skills list, which is strange since the feishu plugin has message sending capabilities built into it. I'm realizing there's a disconnect here - the feishu plugin has message sending capabilities in its code, but the SKILL.md files I can see only cover read operations. Let me reconsider whether there's a feishu-post skill that might be separate from what I'm currently looking at. the issue might be that the backup message and KIIT messages are arriving in the same conversation thread, but the user is looking at a different conversation thread - perhaps one where they're directly messaging the KIIT bot rather than receiving bot-sent messages in the same thread.\n\nI should just explain this directly to the user rather than continuing to debug the message delivery mechanics."},{"type":"text","text":"发现关键事实了：\n\n`cli_a93650c6fc785bce` 这个 app 既是**备份脚本在用的**，也是 **KIIT 的飞书 bot**。两者是同一个 app，理论上发到你 open_id 的消息应该出现在同一个对话里。\n\n但你之前说没收到——可能是这两个原因之一：\n\n**原因 1：消息发到了另一个对话窗口**\n飞书里同一个 bot 和同一个用户之间可以存在多个独立对话（一个是用户主动开的，一个是程序触发的）。备份 bot 发的消息可能掉进了另一个窗口，你没注意到。\n\n**原因 2：消息其实收到了，但没注意到**\n今天凌晨 3:02 那条\"备份完成\"和 3:12 那条\"Evolver 完成\"你应该有收到，只是可能和别的消息混在一起了。\n\n你现在检查一下飞书：搜索\"备份\"或者\"每日任务\"，看能不能找到那两条？\n\n如果找不到，我改用 `sessions_send` 从 kiit 内部直接发消息给你，确保你能在同一个对话里看到。"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776734821109,"responseId":"06360565285d5b96df16e63025a4fc27"}}
