{"type":"message","id":"427c54c7","parentId":"646e7f15","timestamp":"2026-04-21T13:32:24.590Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking if it's worth configuring searxng (searxng) - a privacy-respecting metasearch engine. They're asking if it's necessary/worthwhile for my setup.\n\n Searxng is a self-hosted metasearch engine that aggregates results from multiple search engines without tracking or profiling users. It's useful for privacy, avoiding filter bubbles, and having more control over search data.\n\nGiven my setup as a general-purpose AI assistant that often needs to search the web, searxng could be useful. However, there are some considerations:\n\n1. I already have skills for web search (multi-search-engine, tavily-search, etc.)\n\n\n2. I could run it locally through Docker, though that would require some setup effort\n3. The main advantage would be privacy and avoiding depending on external services\n\nLet me think about what they're really asking - they're suggesting I could set this up for myself, so I should consider whether the benefits of having a private search aggregator outweigh the maintenance work involved."},{"type":"text","text":"有必要，但看你的需求。\n\n**searxng 的优势：**\n- 聚合 Google、Bing、百度等多个搜索引擎，不追踪不画像\n- 完全自建，隐私可控，不被单个搜索引擎的结果绑架\n- 可以替换掉目前一些需要 API key 的搜索服务\n\n**我的现状：**\n- 已有 `multi-search-engine` skill（17 个引擎，不用 API key）\n- 已有 `tavily-search`（需要 key）\n\n**searxng 适合的场景：**\n- 想完全掌控搜索数据，不想走任何第三方\n- 需要更稳定/多样的搜索源（searxng 可连几十个实例）\n- 不想继续用 tavily 的 key 管理\n\n**如果配，方案是：**\n- Docker 起一个 searxng 容器\n- 配置成我的搜索技能的后端\n- 你想现在配，还是先跑一段时间看现有 skill 够不够用再说？"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1776778329672,"responseId":"0636af5a4054826f6e07a81ad547a11b"}}
