* Mark bundle as not supporting multiuse\n< HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden\r\n< content-type: text/html; charset=utf-8\r\n< content-length: 213\r\n< server-timing: total;dur=1.023, render;dur=0\r\n< x-content-type-options: nosniff\r\n< x-download-options: noopen\r\n< x-robots-tag: noindex, nofollow\r\n< referrer-policy: no-referrer\r\n< server: granian\r\n< date: Tue, 21 Apr 2026 14:14:45 GMT\r\n< \r\n{ [213 bytes data]\n\r100   213  100   213    0     0  88639      0 --:--:-- --:--:-- --:--:--  104k\n* Connection #0 to host 192.168.31.146 left intact\n<!doctype html>\n<html lang=en>\n<title>403 Forbidden</title>\n<h1>Forbidden</h1>\n<p>You don&#39;t have the permission to access the requested resource. It is either read-protected or not readable by the server.</p>","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776780885507}}
{"type":"message","id":"be6c6f71","parentId":"a7a33528","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:14:59.560Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still getting 403. The server is `granian` (a Python ASGI server). The 403 is coming from SearXNG itself, not from a network issue.\n\nLooking at the config - `public_instance: false` - this means the instance is not configured as a public instance. This could be why it's blocking API requests.\n\nAlso from the config: `\"limiter\": {\"enabled\": false, ...}` - the limiter is disabled, so it's not IP-based rate limiting.\n\nThe issue might be that:\n1. `public_instance: false` - the instance doesn't want to serve public/API requests\n2. The `search` endpoint might require some form of authentication or initial setup\n\nActually, wait - looking at the SearXNG docs more carefully, there's a `server.maintenance` setting or similar that could block searches.\n\nOr it could be that the SearXNG needs to have its `use_external_openapi` setting enabled.\n\nBut actually, I think the most likely issue is the `public_instance` setting. When `public_instance` is `false`, SearXNG might restrict API access.\n\nLet me try a different approach - check if there's a `POST` endpoint or if there's an issue with the way the limiter works.\n\nActually, let me look at the SearXNG source quickly... The 403 for `/search` when `public_instance: false` is a known behavior in SearXNG. \n\nSearXNG's `public_instance` setting controls whether the instance is accessible to all users or restricted. When disabled, it typically blocks search requests entirely, which explains why we're getting the 403 even though the limiter is off. This is a deliberate security feature to prevent unauthorized usage of private instances."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_o9k6b05ypd7a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"http://192.168.31.146:8888/config\" | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); print('public_instance:', d.get('public_instance')); print('limiter:', json.dumps(d.get('limiter',{}), indent=2))\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776780885524,"responseId":"0636b955331c000fdc6618f85d5f678e"}}
{"type":"message","id":"9a612780","parentId":"be6c6f71","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:14:59.663Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_o9k6b05ypd7a_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"public_instance: False\nlimiter: {\n  \"botdetection.ip_limit.link_token\": false,\n  \"botdetection.ip_lists.pass_searxng_org\": true,\n  \"enabled\": false\n}"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":53,"aggregated":"public_instance: False\nlimiter: {\n  \"botdetection.ip_limit.link_token\": false,\n  \"botdetection.ip_lists.pass_searxng_org\": true,\n  \"enabled\": false\n}","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776780899648}}
{"type":"message","id":"a9b4b4a1","parentId":"9a612780","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:15:09.933Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is `public_instance: false`. SearXNG is not configured as a public instance, which means it restricts access. SearXNG has a \"public_instance\" setting that controls whether the instance is accessible to the public or restricted.\n\nIf `public_instance` is `false`, the instance is in \"private mode\" and requires special access. In this mode, the `search` endpoint might be blocked.\n\nLet me look at the SearXNG documentation to understand what needs to be changed to allow search queries. The setting is likely in the `settings.yml` file inside the container or mounted volume.\n\nActually, looking at the SearXNG source code, when `public_instance` is set to `false`, the instance is typically in \"private mode\" where certain endpoints are restricted. \n\nI need to either set `public_instance: true` in the settings or enable API access through another mechanism. Let me check what the settings.yml file shows for this."},{"type":"text","text":"找到了！`public_instance: false` — SearXNG 默认是私有模式，搜索 API 被限制了。\n\n需要修改 SearXNG 的 `settings.yml`。先看一下容器里的配置：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_1s4bwkg70lk0_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng cat /etc/searxng/settings.yml 2>/dev/null | head -60"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776780899665,"responseId":"0636b9638d75e1b6c30bb240b41fc821"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1816b940","parentId":"a9b4b4a1","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:15:10.089Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_1s4bwkg70lk0_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"general:\n  # Debug mode, only for development. Is overwritten by ${SEARXNG_DEBUG}\n  debug: false\n  # displayed name\n  instance_name: \"SearXNG\"\n  # For example: https://example.com/privacy\n  privacypolicy_url: false\n  # use true to use your own donation page written in searx/info/en/donate.md\n  # use false to disable the donation link\n  donation_url: false\n  # mailto:contact@example.com\n  contact_url: false\n  # record stats\n  enable_metrics: true\n  # expose stats in open metrics format at /metrics\n  # leave empty to disable (no password set)\n  # open_metrics: <password>\n  open_metrics: ''\n\nbrand:\n  docs_url: https://docs.searxng.org/\n  public_instances: https://searx.space\n  wiki_url: https://github.com/searxng/searxng/wiki\n  issue_url: https://github.com/searxng/searxng/issues\n  # custom:\n  #   # Custom entries in the footer: [title]: [link]\n  #   links:\n  #     Uptime: https://uptime.searxng.org/history/darmarit-org\n  #     About: \"https://searxng.org\"\n  # pwa_colors:\n  #   # Custom settings for PWA icon an colors used in manifest.json\n  #   # Default colors are:\n  #    theme_color_light: \"#3050ff\"\n  #    background_color_light: \"fff\"\n  #    theme_color_dark: \"#58f\"\n  #    background_color_dark: \"#222428\"\n  #    theme_color_black: \"#3050ff\"\n  #    background_color_black: \"#000\"\n\nsearch:\n  # Filter results. 0: None, 1: Moderate, 2: Strict\n  safe_search: 0\n  # Existing autocomplete backends: \"360search\", \"baidu\", \"bing\", \"brave\", \"dbpedia\", \"duckduckgo\", \"google\",\n  # \"yandex\", \"mwmbl\", \"naver\", \"seznam\", \"sogou\", \"startpage\", \"swisscows\", \"quark\", \"qwant\", \"wikipedia\" -\n  # leave blank to turn it off by default.\n  autocomplete: \"\"\n  # minimun characters to type before autocompleter starts\n  autocomplete_min: 4\n  # backend for the favicon near URL in search results.\n  # Available resolvers: \"allesedv\", \"duckduckgo\", \"google\", \"yandex\" - leave blank to turn it off by default.\n  favicon_resolver: \"\"\n  # Default search language - leave blank to detect from browser information or\n  # use codes from 'languages.py'\n  default_lang: \"auto\"\n  # max_page: 0  # if engine supports paging, 0 means unlimited numbers of pages\n  # Available languages\n  # languages:\n  #   - all\n  #   - en\n  #   - en-US"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":126,"aggregated":"general:\n  # Debug mode, only for development. Is overwritten by ${SEARXNG_DEBUG}\n  debug: false\n  # displayed name\n  instance_name: \"SearXNG\"\n  # For example: https://example.com/privacy\n  privacypolicy_url: false\n  # use true to use your own donation page written in searx/info/en/donate.md\n  # use false to disable the donation link\n  donation_url: false\n  # mailto:contact@example.com\n  contact_url: false\n  # record stats\n  enable_metrics: true\n  # expose stats in open metrics format at /metrics\n  # leave empty to disable (no password set)\n  # open_metrics: <password>\n  open_metrics: ''\n\nbrand:\n  docs_url: https://docs.searxng.org/\n  public_instances: https://searx.space\n  wiki_url: https://github.com/searxng/searxng/wiki\n  issue_url: https://github.com/searxng/searxng/issues\n  # custom:\n  #   # Custom entries in the footer: [title]: [link]\n  #   links:\n  #     Uptime: https://uptime.searxng.org/history/darmarit-org\n  #     About: \"https://searxng.org\"\n  # pwa_colors:\n  #   # Custom settings for PWA icon an colors used in manifest.json\n  #   # Default colors are:\n  #    theme_color_light: \"#3050ff\"\n  #    background_color_light: \"fff\"\n  #    theme_color_dark: \"#58f\"\n  #    background_color_dark: \"#222428\"\n  #    theme_color_black: \"#3050ff\"\n  #    background_color_black: \"#000\"\n\nsearch:\n  # Filter results. 0: None, 1: Moderate, 2: Strict\n  safe_search: 0\n  # Existing autocomplete backends: \"360search\", \"baidu\", \"bing\", \"brave\", \"dbpedia\", \"duckduckgo\", \"google\",\n  # \"yandex\", \"mwmbl\", \"naver\", \"seznam\", \"sogou\", \"startpage\", \"swisscows\", \"quark\", \"qwant\", \"wikipedia\" -\n  # leave blank to turn it off by default.\n  autocomplete: \"\"\n  # minimun characters to type before autocompleter starts\n  autocomplete_min: 4\n  # backend for the favicon near URL in search results.\n  # Available resolvers: \"allesedv\", \"duckduckgo\", \"google\", \"yandex\" - leave blank to turn it off by default.\n  favicon_resolver: \"\"\n  # Default search language - leave blank to detect from browser information or\n  # use codes from 'languages.py'\n  default_lang: \"auto\"\n  # max_page: 0  # if engine supports paging, 0 means unlimited numbers of pages\n  # Available languages\n  # languages:\n  #   - all\n  #   - en\n  #   - en-US","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776780910074}}
