{"type":"message","id":"a5dc27e8","parentId":"c3071faf","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:17:12.769Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The container is listening on port 8888 (both IPv4 and IPv6), and the port mapping looks correct. But curl on the local machine can't connect. Wait - the Docker host is `halei-Surface-Pro-4`, and the SearXNG is running in Docker on the same machine at 192.168.31.146. If curl is connecting from the local machine (halei-Surface-Pro-4) to 192.168.31.146:8888, it should work if 192.168.31.146 is the IP of the machine.\n\nBut wait - I'm running these commands on the local machine (halei-Surface-Pro-4), and 192.168.31.146 is probably the IP of that same machine on the local network. \n\nActually, the connection refused error means the port isn't reachable at all, which suggests the Docker container might not be binding to the external interface properly or there's a firewall blocking the connection. Let me try connecting to localhost instead."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9oquqpie1pj5_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s \"http://localhost:8888/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=3\" 2>&1 | head -30"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781023783,"responseId":"0636b9e012339c4cb213edd3a5ea6288"}}
