{"type":"message","id":"871ca518","parentId":"14583728","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:17:34.747Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still 429. The limiter is blocking based on the real IP regardless of X-Forwarded-For. Let me check the limiter configuration more carefully. The issue is that `public_instance: true` requires the limiter, and the limiter requires Redis/Valkey. But even with Valkey running, the limiter is still blocking requests.\n\nLet me check if the limiter.toml file is needed. The error said \"missing config file: /etc/searxng/limiter.toml\". Maybe I need to create it.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach. Instead of fighting with the limiter, let me set `public_instance: false` but enable the engines that work (arch linux wiki, wikipedia, etc.) and use `enable_http: true` for engines. This avoids the limiter entirely."},{"type":"text","text":"Limiter 配置缺失导致全面拒绝。先绕过它——把 `public_instance` 改回 false，单独开启引擎：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tvyl9rhn7rup_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng sed -i 's/  public_instance: true/  public_instance: false/' /etc/searxng/settings.yml && docker exec searxng grep \"public_instance\" /etc/searxng/settings.yml"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781045823,"responseId":"0636b9f63fead1a7d5a871cf1b555296"}}
