{"type":"message","id":"e61fafe1","parentId":"2673342f","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:23:47.975Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see `valkey.url: false` which is the default. The limter.toml is missing, but we disabled limiter so it shouldn't matter.\n\nThe 403 Forbidden is really puzzling. Let me think about this more carefully.\n\nThe SearXNG binary runs inside the container on port 8080 (internal). The Docker port mapping forwards 8888 → 8080.\n\nWhen I do `docker exec searxng wget http://127.0.0.1:8080/...`, the request goes to the SearXNG application running inside the container. The app is returning 403.\n\nLooking at the logs:\n```\n2026-04-21 14:23:16,107 WARNING:searx.botdetection.config: missing config file: /etc/searxng/limiter.toml\n\n\n```\n\nEven though I set `limiter: false` in settings.yml, the botdetection module is still looking for limiter.toml. This suggests the newer version of SearXNG might have botdetection running independently of the limiter setting. But the real issue is why the 403 is happening in the first place. Let me check if there's something about how the binary is built or if there's an IP-based access control mechanism I'm missing. Actually, I'm noticing something interesting—the latest version has `limiter: true` in the default settings, yet the container isn't using the `SEARXNG_LIMITER` environment variable that was causing problems before.\n\nThe key difference is that we're now using a Docker named volume (`searxng-config`) for persistence instead of bind mounts. With a volume, the initial settings.yml gets created from the image's default, and when I modify it, those changes persist in the volume. Let me verify what's actually in the volume right now.\n\n```"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_or6n6g3n4khn_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng grep -n \"public_instance\\|limiter:\" /etc/searxng/settings.yml"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781414580,"responseId":"0636bb663c3ea11a73c3b99965ce3e4f"}}
