{"type":"message","id":"fbfd3477","parentId":"c7c8caf3","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:23:58.688Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So public_instance is false and limiter is false. But we still get 403. Let me check if there's an `enable_http` setting that needs to be on for outbound requests, or if there's something in the outgoing section blocking things.\n\nWait - looking at the log again: \"WARNING: searx.botdetection.config: missing config file: /etc/searxng/limiter.toml\" - this is just a warning, not the error.\n\nThe 403 is puzzling. Let me look at the actual HTTP response headers when we get a 403 to understand what's happening.\n\nActually, wait. Let me check if the issue is something simpler - maybe the engines themselves are returning 403 because they can't reach the internet. \n\nI should check the Docker logs to see if there are any outbound errors when engines try to make requests. Looking back at the initial startup log, I noticed DuckDuckGo had a connection timeout error. The 403 we're getting now might actually be the engines failing and SearXNG returning a 403 response with no results rather than blocking the request itself. Let me try making a direct search request to see what response we get."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_pghjm39ahw49_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng wget -O - \"http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=1\" -v 2>&1 | grep -E \"HTTP|< |>|403|200\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781428097,"responseId":"0636bb7441d1dbda74548b67c60e250b"}}
