{"type":"message","id":"a9b05ac8","parentId":"85123dc1","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:24:33.218Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"OK so even the homepage works (200 OK) but the /search endpoint returns 403 with format=json. This is very strange.\n\nLet me think about what could cause this specific behavior:\n1. The 403 is from the SearXNG application itself, not from a proxy/firewall\n2. The homepage renders fine\n3. The /search endpoint with format=json returns 403\n\nIn SearXNG, when public_instance is set to false, the /search endpoint may require a special header or token. Let me check if there's an `image_proxy` or similar setting that needs to be enabled.\n\nActually wait - I just realized something. Let me check the SearXNG version and whether there's a known issue with JSON format and 403 in the latest version.\n\nActually, I just thought of something important. Let me look at the error more carefully. The 403 Forbidden for `/search` when using `format=json` but not for the HTML homepage...\n \nI'm wondering if the `format` parameter itself might be getting blocked by a filter or bot protection mechanism in the latest SearXNG version. Let me try removing that parameter to see if JSON output works without it."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jdm6a36p7m7l_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng wget -O - \"http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw\" --header \"User-Agent: Mozilla/5.0\" 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781460716,"responseId":"0636bb95f45d4874b72fe2877dfcd069"}}
