{"type":"message","id":"0aed1e18","parentId":"f69d7833","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:24:48.083Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! HTML search works (200 OK), but JSON format returns 403 Forbidden. This strongly suggests that the JSON format (`format=json`) requires either:\n1. API key / token\n2. Authenticated session\n3. A specific endpoint that's restricted\n\nLet me check if there's an API endpoint or authentication required for JSON output. Let me also look at the SearXNG source code to understand this.\n\nActually, wait - this might be the bot detection / limiter even though `limiter: false` in settings.yml. The `public_instance: true` is what enables the stricter checks. With `public_instance: false` but JSON still blocked, maybe there's something else.\n\nActually, let me try without the `format=json` and just get HTML results - that works! So the issue is specifically with the JSON format.\n\n\nI should check the SearXNG documentation to see if there's special authentication configured for JSON responses, or maybe try a GET request instead of wget to see if that makes a difference."},{"type":"text","text":"HTML 搜索通了（200）！只有 `format=json` 被拦。问题出在 JSON 格式的访问控制。\n\n试下直接 curl 而非 wget：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_nus5uqtauu07_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng curl -s \"http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" 2>&1 | head -15"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781476487,"responseId":"0636bba44f66e3ffe90daf460dd1ce8a"}}
