{"type":"message","id":"67d42d98","parentId":"b489076e","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:25:02.421Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! Even from inside the container with Python, JSON format returns 403. But HTML works fine. This suggests there's some request body/content-length issue or some header check that specifically affects the JSON format.\n\nLet me check if there's something about the SEARXNG_BASE_URL that might be causing this - since we're accessing via 127.0.0.1:8080 but SEARXNG_BASE_URL is set to http://192.168.31.146:8888.\n\nWait actually - the JSON response might be checking the Referer or Origin header against SEARXNG_BASE_URL. Let me try with the correct Host header."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_hnihh380l1sp_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng python3 -c \"\nimport urllib.request, json\nurl = 'http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2'\nreq = urllib.request.Request(url, headers={\n    'User-Agent': 'Mozilla/5.0',\n    'Host': '192.168.31.146:8888',\n    'Referer': 'http://192.168.31.146:8888/'\n})\ntry:\n    with urllib.request.urlopen(req, timeout=10) as r:\n        data = json.loads(r.read())\n        print('OK:', list(data.keys()))\nexcept Exception as e:\n    print('ERROR:', e)\n\""}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781493822,"responseId":"0636bbb6f5a143d0e2cb5177ab4f3b45"}}
