{"type":"message","id":"09cfd1ad","parentId":"e234ad69","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:25:59.575Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is that when `SEARXNG_BASE_URL` is set to `http://192.168.31.146:8888`, but the container's internal port is 8080, and the mapping is `8888:8888`, the internal service is on port 8080 but the external URL references port 8888.\n\nThe `public_instance: false` makes the `/search` endpoint only accessible from localhost on the internal port 8080. The JSON format endpoint specifically checks that the Host/referrer matches the base_url.\n\nLet me look at this from a different angle. The `public_instance: false` setting restricts the JSON API. Let me try enabling public_instance but without the limiter (since the limiter crashes with the latest version). \n\nActually, thinking about it more - `public_instance: false` means the instance is private, and the JSON API is restricted to localhost. \n\nBut the HTML form search works fine, so the issue is specifically with JSON format. I could enable `public_instance: true` and disable the limiter separately, which would allow the JSON API without the rate limiting component that's causing the crash. I could try bypassing the limiter issue entirely by setting up a reverse proxy with Nginx to handle rate limiting instead, since the limiter and Valkey setup seem problematic in this Docker environment.\n\nBut actually, the real blocker is that `public_instance: false` restricts the JSON API to localhost only. If I enable `public_instance: true`, it forces the limiter on regardless of the config file setting, and since the limiter requires Valkey and crashes, I need to find a way to get the JSON API accessible while managing the rate limiting separately.\n\nLooking at this more carefully, I could disable public_instance in settings.yml but set the `SEARXNG_LIMITER` environment variable to false to prevent it from being forced on. Alternatively, I should test whether the HTML search actually returns results or if it's also failing, and then check what happens when I use a different User-Agent."},{"type":"text","text":"HTML 搜索通，JSON 不通——`public_instance: false` 下 JSON API 被限制为仅本地访问。试下环境变量强制关闭 limiter：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_794eog8fnst7_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker stop searxng\ndocker run -d \\\n  --name searxng \\\n  -p 8888:8888 \\\n  -e SEARXNG_BASE_URL=\"http://192.168.31.146:8888/\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_LIMITER=\"false\" \\\n  -v searxng-config:/etc/searxng \\\n  --restart unless-stopped \\\n  searxng/searxng:latest\n\nsleep 6\ndocker exec searxng grep -E \"public_instance|limiter:\" /etc/searxng/settings.yml\ndocker exec searxng wget -O - \"http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781540747,"responseId":"0636bbe5b741aa4e4c8e63af2db2516b"}}
