{"type":"message","id":"469eb4dd","parentId":"8c81bd6c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:26:42.056Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `SEARXNG_LIMITER=false` is correctly set, `limiter: false` in settings, `public_instance: false`. Still 403.\n\nThis is a very specific block. Let me check if there's a network-level block on the host. The machine is at 192.168.31.146, which is the same IP as the SearXNG instance. But this host machine is also at 192.168.31.146, so when I try to connect to 192.168.31.146:8888 from the host itself, it's connecting to itself through the network - which might be blocked at the network interface level.\n \nI'm wondering if the `-h 192.168.31.146` bind option would help since it explicitly tells the server to listen on that interface, but the real issue seems to be that this machine is both the host and the SearXNG server. When curl makes a request to 192.168.31.146:8888, it's hitting the public interface of this very machine. The docker port mapping shows 0.0.0.0:8888->8888/tcp, so it should be accessible, but something in the network stack or firewall is blocking the JSON format specifically.\n\nLet me check if iptables is interfering, and also verify whether `public_instance: false` is actually preventing all non-localhost JSON requests instead of just external ones. I should test if adding the Host header or accessing via 127.0.0.1 works differently than the direct IP connection.\n\nThe Python script in the container failed with a 403 on the JSON format request, which is odd since wget from the same container worked fine—that suggests the issue isn't network-level but something in how the request is being processed internally.\n\nLooking at the wget output more carefully, it's hitting 127.0.0.1 successfully while the Python urllib request might be resolving differently. Could be a DNS or routing issue where 127.0.0.1 doesn't consistently route to the container's internal interface, so I should try using the Docker bridge gateway instead."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p91rvdd8av3t_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng wget -O - \"http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" 2>&1\necho \"---\"\n# Also check if the network works from the host\ncurl -s \"http://127.0.0.1:8888/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" 2>&1 | head -5"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781583793,"responseId":"0636bc10f0f3c25c249bf387cf5762e0"}}
