{"type":"message","id":"abc2fada","parentId":"a9c2a305","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:27:25.816Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The server is listening on port 8080 inside the container, and the host maps 8888 to 8080. So from outside the container, the search API should be accessible via `http://192.168.31.146:8888/search?q=...&format=json`. But the curl is getting connection refused... wait, no - the curl from inside the exec returns 403, not connection refused. But the curl from the host earlier returned \"connection refused\" to 192.168.31.146:8888.\n\nWait, the host's curl to localhost:8888 returned empty (not an error). That means it connected but got an empty response. Let me try that again.\n\nActually wait - from the host: `curl -s \"http://127.0.0.1:8888/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\"` returned empty (no output). \n\nSo I'm getting different responses depending on where the request originates: wget from inside the container gets a 403 on the JSON format, curl from the host gets an empty response, and curl to the LAN IP gets connection refused. That's odd—let me test curl from the host again to see what's actually happening."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_yo4021xtfq8f_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -sv \"http://127.0.0.1:8888/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781635358,"responseId":"0636bc4357e7e2b6131d0c67d3c60633"}}
