{"type":"message","id":"82ab6e5c","parentId":"e4fea692","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:33:05.621Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Port 8888 IS listening on all interfaces. But curl to 192.168.31.146:8888 gets no output. This is really strange.\n\nWait - could there be a firewall or network policy that's blocking the connection? Or maybe Docker's iptables rules are interfering.\n\nActually wait - earlier I got \"Connection refused\" when curling to 192.168.31.146:8888. But now I'm getting \"no output\" which is different from \"connection refused\". No output means the connection was established but nothing was received.\n\nLet me try with a longer timeout and see what happens."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_snszw74r4lba_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl --connect-timeout 5 -v \"http://192.168.31.146:8888/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" 2>&1 | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781978361,"responseId":"0636bd9a21c3ca3ddae5f90cb210d0e2"}}
