{"type":"message","id":"11d1a18a","parentId":"d7c1426c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:33:16.637Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very strange. The port 8888 is listening on 0.0.0.0 but curl to 192.168.31.146:8888 fails with \"Connection refused\" immediately. \n\nWait... the `ss` output shows the listening socket, but it could be from a previous process. Let me check what process owns that port.\n\nActually wait - could it be a firewall issue? Or maybe Docker's userland proxy?\n\nLet me try connecting to 127.0.0.1:8888 from the host:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_p6gtkuckhv1i_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl --connect-timeout 3 -v \"http://127.0.0.1:8888/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" 2>&1 | head -15"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781990598,"responseId":"0636bda6dfb5c95f3ff5705f2ca2b77b"}}
