{"type":"message","id":"5aff9cdc","parentId":"6aae7dbd","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:33:33.492Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Very strange - the port is listening (ss shows it) but curl gets an empty reply. And wget from inside the container also gets 403. This is very confusing.\n\nWait, actually I just realized something. The ss output shows the socket is listening on 0.0.0.0:8888, which means it's accepting connections. But curl gets \"Empty reply from server\". This might be because:\n\n1. The granian server is in a broken state\n2. There's something wrong with the SearXNG application itself\n\nLet me check if there's a worker process that's actually handling requests, or if the worker crashed.\n\nActually, let me try a completely different approach. Instead of fighting with the JSON API, let me:\n\n\n1. Just parse the HTML results directly (since HTML search works)\n2. Or use a different approach altogether\n\nActually wait - I just had a breakthrough idea. What if the 403 on JSON is actually coming from the **engine-level bot detection**, not from SearXNG's own access control? What if individual engines like Google/DuckDuckGo are returning 403 responses, and SearXNG is just passing those through? That would mean the HTML search works because it renders differently, but the JSON API fails because it can't properly handle or mask the engine errors.\n\nBut that doesn't quite fit either - we'd still expect some JSON response from SearXNG itself, even if the results are empty or contain error messages. Let me try the HTML approach first since that actually works, or maybe switch to GET requests instead of POST to see if that changes anything.\n\nActually, I'm noticing the settings show `method: \"POST\"` by default, but the HTML search works fine as GET requests. The issue might be that JSON requests require POST while the URL parameters aren't being processed correctly, or there's something about how the Content-Length header is being handled. Let me try a POST request with JSON to see if that bypasses whatever's blocking the GET requests."},{"type":"text","text":"网络层通了但应用层响应为空。可能是 POST 模式的问题，换个方法试：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_z2w1gn0mov0a_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"# Try POST method (settings says method: POST)\ncurl -s -X POST \"http://127.0.0.1:8888/search\" \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded\" \\\n  -d \"q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" | head -20"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776781996688,"responseId":"0636bdacec2f710c725eece8a843af9f"}}
