{"type":"message","id":"da6a964b","parentId":"1b5f8f83","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:34:02.265Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Still 403 from Python inside the container! This is very strange. The container's own Python urllib can't access the SearXNG app running on port 8080 inside the container.\n\nWait - but `wget http://127.0.0.1:8080/` worked and returned HTML. And `wget http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=...` without format=json returned 200 HTML. But format=json gets 403.\n\nLet me check if maybe the 403 is coming from the engine itself, not from SearXNG's access control. Maybe the engines (Google, etc.) are blocked by the Chinese network, and when the engine returns an error, SearXNG returns 403?\n \nActually, that doesn't make sense. Access control 403 and engine 403 would be indistinguishable at the HTTP level. Let me try switching to GET method instead and see if that helps."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_38qx47obx1of_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng sed -i 's/^  method: \"POST\"/  method: \"GET\"/' /etc/searxng/settings.yml\ndocker exec searxng grep \"method\" /etc/searxng/settings.yml\ndocker restart searxng && sleep 6"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776782032854,"responseId":"0636bdd12e429e9635182a2aa057085f"}}
