{"type":"message","id":"37eadebf","parentId":"ded1ce12","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:38:19.288Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is very strange. The settings.yml is being applied correctly (bind_address: 0.0.0.0, method: GET), but curl to 127.0.0.1:8888 gets an empty reply.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. Maybe the issue is that the granian server starts, binds to 0.0.0.0:8080 inside the container, and the docker port mapping works. But somehow the connection gets closed immediately.\n\nActually, wait - I just realized something. Earlier today when I first started the container with a named volume (`searxng-config:/etc/searxng`), the port worked (I could see from wget inside the container getting 403 instead of empty). \n\nBut now there's no volume, so the default settings apply. Maybe the previous searxng instance was actually working through the port mapping but I just wasn't testing it correctly, or perhaps there's something else going on with how the volume configuration affects the startup behavior.\n\nLet me check what's happening inside the container right now - maybe the settings file isn't being read properly or granian is binding to a different interface than expected. I should test the connection from within the container itself to see if the service is actually listening on the port."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8lduhgug8nsa_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng wget -O - \"http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=1\" 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776782288083,"responseId":"0636bed0e7aaa0b6b9d6d2759dbed270"}}
