{"type":"message","id":"547a79f2","parentId":"7c01c195","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:38:37.104Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So inside the container, the SearXNG app is returning 403 for JSON requests. This is the core issue. It's not a networking problem at all - the app itself is blocking JSON searches.\n\nLet me look at the latest SearXNG source code changes. The `public_instance: false` setting blocks JSON API access. But wait - in the latest version, there might be a different mechanism.\n\nLooking at the settings again - `public_instance: false` and `method: POST` in the container's default settings. Let me check if there's a specific setting to enable JSON API access without going through the UI.\n\nActually, wait. I just realized something. In older SearXNG versions, the settings.yml had `public_instance: false` by default and the JSON API still worked (just with some restrictions). But the 403 error suggests the server is actively blocking it.\n \nMaybe I should try configuring a `SEARXNG_JSON_PROXY` environment variable instead, or look into how the 2024.6.0 release changed the API access control. Actually, I just noticed the error log mentions a missing `limiter.toml` file - that might be the blocker. But the real issue is that `public_instance: false` itself is preventing JSON API access, so I need to set `public_instance: true` to get it working. But when I do that with `limiter: true`, it crashes due to the granian/Python threading issue. Let me try the latest approach instead.\n\nActually, I'm realizing the config changes aren't persisting across container restarts because of the volume mount. I should check whether the volume has a `searxng-config` that's storing the old settings. Let me bypass the volume entirely and configure it through environment variables instead."},{"type":"text","text":"容器内的 SearXNG 一直返回 403，不是网络问题是应用层限制。`public_instance: false` 禁用了 JSON API，但开启它又触发 limiter 导致崩溃。\n\n用环境变量来控制，绕过这个冲突：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_2s8yf7bgzdq6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker rm -f searxng 2>/dev/null\n\ndocker run -d \\\n  --name searxng \\\n  -p 8888:8888 \\\n  -e SEARXNG_BASE_URL=\"http://127.0.0.1:8888/\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_SECRET=\"KiitSearch2024\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_PUBLIC_INSTANCE=\"true\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_LIMITER=\"false\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_METHOD=\"GET\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_BIND_ADDRESS=\"0.0.0.0\" \\\n  --restart unless-stopped \\\n  searxng/searxng:latest\n\nsleep 8\ndocker exec searxng wget -O - \"http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=2\" 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776782299450,"responseId":"0636bedbac82e2347cdecb85993ca9f8"}}
