{"type":"message","id":"b60d5109","parentId":"652a6da9","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:38:49.289Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_ufmpyealdcno_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"File \"/usr/lib/python3.14/concurrent/futures/thread.py\", line 37, in <module>\n    threading._register_atexit(_python_exit)\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.14/threading.py\", line 1546, in _register_atexit\n    raise RuntimeError(\"can't register atexit after shutdown\")\nRuntimeError: can't register atexit after shutdown\n[ERROR] Unexpected exit from worker-1\n[INFO] Shutting down granian\nSearXNG 2026.4.17-e8299a4c3\nUpdating certificates in /etc/ssl/certs..."}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":71,"aggregated":"File \"/usr/lib/python3.14/concurrent/futures/thread.py\", line 37, in <module>\n    threading._register_atexit(_python_exit)\n    ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/usr/lib/python3.14/threading.py\", line 1546, in _register_atexit\n    raise RuntimeError(\"can't register atexit after shutdown\")\nRuntimeError: can't register atexit after shutdown\n[ERROR] Unexpected exit from worker-1\n[INFO] Shutting down granian\nSearXNG 2026.4.17-e8299a4c3\nUpdating certificates in /etc/ssl/certs...","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1776782329272}}
{"type":"message","id":"fb9bd0cf","parentId":"b60d5109","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:38:57.573Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"`SEARXNG_PUBLIC_INSTANCE=\"true\"` causes the worker to crash immediately with the granian/Python 3.14 threading error. This is a known bug in the latest version when `public_instance` is true.\n\nSo the issue is:\n- `public_instance: false` → JSON API disabled (403)\n- `public_instance: true` → Worker crashes (granian threading error)\n\nThere's no way around this with the current image version. The solution is to use an older version of SearXNG that doesn't have this bug.\n\nLet me try a completely different approach - use a docker-compose file with a specific older version tag that we know works. Let me try to pull version 2024.10.0 or similar."},{"type":"text","text":"`public_instance=true` 在这个版本会触发 granian 崩溃。换旧版本：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_j7zk73ft0yf9_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker pull docker.io/searxng/searxng:2025.1.15 2>&1 | tail -3","yieldMs":30000}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776782329295,"responseId":"0636bef94607a668bd01b05b09c5a7c1"}}
