{"type":"message","id":"b35e474f","parentId":"644daa2c","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:39:57.385Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Docker Hub 拉取一直超时。让我 try a different approach. Instead of using public_instance=true, let me try to use the limiter properly with valkey. The issue earlier was that when we enabled limiter, it required valkey but then the worker crashed.\n\nActually, wait. Let me look at the error again: `RuntimeError: can't register atexit after shutdown` - this is happening when `public_instance: true` is set, which then forces the usage of limiter. The limiter needs valkey. We have valkey running. Let me check why the limiter was crashing.\n\nActually the crash happened because: when public_instance=true, it tries to use limiter. Limiter needs valkey. But actually, looking at the earlier test where I added the valkey sidecar and the limiter.toml file, the issue was that the granian worker was crashing with the threading error at startup, BEFORE valkey was even contacted.\n\nSo this is a bug in SearXNG 2026.4.17 with Python 3.14's threading and granian. The `public_instance: true` setting activates code paths that trigger this bug.\n\nThe real solution is to either:\n\n\n1. Use an older version of SearXNG (before 2026.4)\n2. Fix the public_instance=false issue differently\n\nFor option 2, I need to understand why public_instance=false blocks JSON API. Let me re-read the source... Actually, the issue is that when public_instance is false, there's a different access restriction. Let me try to access it using the correct Host header that matches the BASE_URL.\n\nActually, thinking about this more carefully: The 403 when using public_instance=false happens when format=json is requested. This is documented behavior - when public_instance=false, the JSON API is restricted to localhost only. But from inside the container, wget to 127.0.0.1:8080 also gives 403. That's the real puzzle - I'm inside the container hitting localhost, yet still getting blocked. Something about how the limiter or access control is being applied doesn't match the documentation."},{"type":"text","text":"Docker Hub 拉取超时。先换个思路——`public_instance: false` 的 JSON 限制是针对\"非本地\"请求。让我从容器内部完全模拟本地请求：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_29c0aabixc26_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker rm -f searxng 2>/dev/null\ndocker run -d \\\n  --name searxng \\\n  -p 8888:8888 \\\n  -e SEARXNG_BASE_URL=\"http://127.0.0.1:8888/\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_METHOD=\"GET\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_LIMITER=\"false\" \\\n  -e SEARXNG_PUBLIC_INSTANCE=\"false\" \\\n  --restart unless-stopped \\\n  searxng/searxng:latest\n\nsleep 7\n# Check what the actual settings are in the container\ndocker exec searxng grep -E \"public_instance|bind_address|method\" /etc/searxng/settings.yml | head -5\n# Now try from inside container\ndocker exec searxng wget -O - \"http://127.0.0.1:8080/search?q=openclaw&format=json&limit=1\" 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776782377861,"responseId":"0636bf2a2960f06d40c00770d1f22546"}}
