{"type":"message","id":"10fccfff","parentId":"ecaa4f93","timestamp":"2026-04-21T14:40:16.123Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The env vars are NOT overriding the settings.yml. The env vars `SEARXNG_METHOD`, `SEARXNG_LIMITER`, `SEARXNG_PUBLIC_INSTANCE` are not being read. This is because when there's a volume mount (`searxng-config:/etc/searxng`), the settings in the volume take precedence over env vars. But we're NOT mounting a volume now, so the settings.yml should be the default one.\n\nWait - the container keeps reverting to `bind_address: \"127.0.0.1\"` and `method: \"POST\"`. This means either:\n1. The settings.yml inside the image has these defaults (and env vars don't override them)\n\n\n2. Or there's something resetting them\n\nI think the settings.yml in the image itself defaults to `bind_address: \"127.0.0.1\"` and `method: \"POST\"`, and since we're not mounting a volume, the container should be using the image's default settings. But the env vars like `SEARXNG_METHOD`, `SEARXNG_BIND_ADDRESS`, and `SEARXNG_LIMITER` should be overriding what's in the YAML file. Yet they're not taking effect at all.\n\nThe real problem might be that granian isn't even starting—the connection got refused when I tried to connect to port 8080, and the logs don't show granian successfully spawning a worker, which suggests the server might be failing to start entirely."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_kjgd8q7bwo5b_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"docker exec searxng ss -tlnp 2>/dev/null"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1776782405058,"responseId":"0636bf45e0dcb5f6e7f7c32ceb418b07"}}
